understanding. There being no mutuality, the purchaser could not ask for the remedy of spe-
cific enforcement under S. 15, Specific Relief Act, 1963; S.M. Gopal Chetty v Raman, AIR
1998 Mad 169. Every agreement has not to be in writing. It must be bilateral, Tarsem Singh
v Sukhminder Singh, (1998) 3 SCC 471: AIR 1998 SC 1400. Writing is necessary only when
