In India also there has been a great divergence of opinion in the courts as
to how far a stranger to a contract can enforce it. There are many decided
cases which declare that a contract cannot be enforced by a person who is
not a party to it and that the rule in Tweddle v Atkinson is as much appli-
cable in India as it is in England. But there is no provision in the Contract
Act either for or against the rule. The Privy Council extended the rule to
India in its decision in Jamna Das v Pandit Ram Autar Pande."
