3. Doctrine of restitution
If an infant obtains property or goods by misrepresenting his age, he can
be compelled to restore it, but only so long as the same is traceable in his
possession. This is known as the equitable doctrine of restitution. Where the
infant has sold the goods or converted them, he cannot be made to repay
the value of the goods, because that would amount to enforcing a void con-
tract. Again, the doctrine of restitution is not applied where the infant has
obtained cash instead of goods. The well-known authority is Leslie (R) Ltd
