truth, either uphold the contract or reject it. If he confirms it, the contract
becomes binding on both the parties. It is a contract which is enforceable at
the option of only one of the parties, namely, the party whose consent was
not free. Giving the meaning of a voidable contract, Section 2(i) says that
"an agreement which is enforceable by law at the option of one or more of
the parties thereto, but not at the option of the other or others, is a voidable
contract.²
