3. Fraudulent
An agreement made for a "fraudulent" purpose is void. Where the par-
ties agree to impose a fraud on a third person, their agreement is unlawful.
Where, for example, a debtor agreed to pay a separate commission, or to
give preference to a creditor in order to induce his consent to a composi-
