Contingency to be condition precedent
Generally, the condition which is collateral to the performance of a con-
tract is a condition precedent, that is, it has to be satisfied first and then
performance can be demanded. It has to be distinguished from a condition
subsequent, namely, a condition which has to be satisfied after the forma-
