Order of performance
The order in which reciprocal promises must be performed may be fixed
by the contract and the order so fixed must be followed. But where the order
is not expressly fixed, they will have to be performed in the order which the
nature of the transaction admits. The relevant provision is Section 52.
S. 52. Order of performance of reciprocal promises.-Where the order
in which reciprocal promises are to be performed is expressly fixed by the con-
tract, they shall be performed in that order; and where the order is not expressly
fixed by the contract, they shall be performed in that order which the nature of
the transaction requires.
