the claim. The original contract must be so discharged by the opposite party
that the plaintiff is entitled to treat himself as free from the obligation of
further performance and he must have elected to do so. The remedy is not
available to the party who breaks the contract even though he might have
partly performed it. The remedy is restitutory, it is a recompense for the
