that behalf, or otherwise making it plain by his conduct that he will there-
after insist upon them. But there are cases where no withdrawal is possible.
It may be too late to withdraw; or it cannot be done without injustice to the
other party. In that case he is bound by his waiver. He will not be allowed
to revert to his strict legal rights. He can only enforce them subject to the
waiver he has made."
