The theory on which quasi-contractual obligations are based is not yet
finally settled. Lord MANSFIELD who is considered to be the real founder of
such obligations, explained them on the principle that law as well as justice
should try to prevent "unjust enrichment", that is, enrichment of one person
at the cost of another. His Lordship offered this explanation in Moses v
Macferlan:¹
