5. Mistake or coercion [S. 72]
Section 72 deals with payments made or things delivered under mistake
or coercion.
S. 72. Liability of person to whom money is paid, or thing delivered,
by mistake or under coercion.-A person to whom money has been paid, or
anything delivered, by mistake or under coercion, must repay or return it.
Illustrations
(a) A and B jointly owe 100 rupees to C. A alone pays the amount to C, and B, not knowing
this fact, pays 100 rupees over again to C. C is bound to repay the amount to B.
