QUASI-CONTRACTS IN ENGLISH LAW
The variety of quasi-contractual obligations recognised by English Law
may now be noted.
Payments to the defendant's use
Two principles seem to govern this kind of quasi-contractual liability.
One of them is that the payment should have been made under pressure and
not voluntarily and the other is that the defendant should have been bound
to pay and has been relieved of his liability by the payment made by the
plaintiff.
