S. 139. Discharge of surety by creditor's act or omission impairing
surety's eventual remedy.-If the creditor does any act which is inconsistent
with the right of the surety, or omits to do any act which his duty to the surety
requires him to do, and the eventual remedy of the surety himself against the
principal debtor is thereby impaired, the surety is discharged.
Illustrations
(a) B contracts to build a ship for C for a given sum, to be paid by instalments as the work
