make compensation to B for the injury to the horse.
Goods must be used by the bailee strictly for the purpose for which they
have been bailed to him. Any unauthorised use of the goods would make the
bailee absolutely liable for any loss of or damage to the goods. Even an act
of God or inevitable accident would be no defence. A horse lent for riding
should not be used for any other purpose and if it is used outside the scope
of the bailment, the bailee would be liable for any damage to the horse how-
