also the requirement of mutuality has been subjected to such a large number
of exceptions that it has been observed in CHITTY: "the number and impor-
tance of these exceptions has given rise to a doubt as to the existence of the
requirement of mutuality."212 The provisions of Section 12 are sufficient in
themselves to rid the law of the requirement of mutuality. That section has
been further supported by this sub-section which quite clearly says that the
court should not decline specific relief only because of lack of mutuality.
