(iii) Further relief where plaintiff entitled to it (proviso)
All that the proviso to Section 34 of the Specific Relief Act forbids is a suit
for mere declaration without further relief if the plaintiff can sue for further
relief. The term "further relief" means "the relief to which the plaintiff is
necessarily entitled on the basis of declaration of the title". This is done in
order to avoid multiplicity of suits. Further, relief must be in relation to the
legal character or right to such character or the right which the defendant
